swAclMgmtMIB.name: swAclMgmtMIB
swAclMgmtMIB.description: The structure of Access Control List information for the proprietary enterprise.

Ipv6Address.name: Ipv6Address
Ipv6Address.description: This data type is used to model IPv6 addresses. This is a binary string of 16 octets in network byte-order.

swCpuInterfacefilterState.name: swCpuInterfacefilterState
swCpuInterfacefilterState.description: Enable or disable CPU Interface Filtering (also called Software ACL). The default is disabled. If enabled, the filtering entries in the swAclRuleMgmt tables will be set to active if its RuleSwAclState is enabled. If disabled, the software ACL function will be disabled.

swACLTotalUsedRuleEntries.name: swACLTotalUsedRuleEntries
swACLTotalUsedRuleEntries.description: The total number of used ACL rule entries.

swACLTotalUnusedRuleEntries.name: swACLTotalUnusedRuleEntries
swACLTotalUnusedRuleEntries.description: The total number of unused ACL rule entries.

swACLEthernetTable.name: swACLEthernetTable
swACLEthernetTable.description: This table contains ACL mask Ethernet information. The access profile will be created on the switch to define which part of each incoming frame's layer 2 header will be examined by the switch. Masks entered will be combined with the values the switch finds in the specified frame header fields.

swACLEthernetEntry.name: swACLEthernetEntry
swACLEthernetEntry.description: A list of information about the ACL for Ethernet.

swACLEthernetProfileID.name: swACLEthernetProfileID
swACLEthernetProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL mask entry unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swACLEthernetUsevlan.name: swACLEthernetUsevlan
swACLEthernetUsevlan.description: Specifies that the switch will examine the VLAN part of each packet header.

swACLEthernetMacAddrMaskState.name: swACLEthernetMacAddrMaskState
swACLEthernetMacAddrMaskState.description: This object indicates the status of the MAC address mask. other (1) - Neither source MAC address nor destination MAC address are masked. dst-mac-addr (2) - Destination MAC addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the MAC address entry for the table. src-mac-addr (3) - Source MAC addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the MAC address entry for the table. dst-src-mac-addr (4) - Source or destination MAC addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the MAC address entry of the table.

swACLEthernetSrcMacAddrMask.name: swACLEthernetSrcMacAddrMask
swACLEthernetSrcMacAddrMask.description: This object specifies the MAC address mask for the source MAC address.

swACLEthernetDstMacAddrMask.name: swACLEthernetDstMacAddrMask
swACLEthernetDstMacAddrMask.description: This object specifies the MAC address mask for the destination MAC address.

swACLEthernetUse8021p.name: swACLEthernetUse8021p
swACLEthernetUse8021p.description: Specifies if the switch will examine the 802.1p priority value in the frame's header or not.

swACLEthernetUseEthernetType.name: swACLEthernetUseEthernetType
swACLEthernetUseEthernetType.description: Specifies if the switch will examine the Ethernet type value in each frame's header or not.

swACLEthernetRowStatus.name: swACLEthernetRowStatus
swACLEthernetRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swACLEthernetOwner.name: swACLEthernetOwner
swACLEthernetOwner.description: The owner of the ACL mask entry. The type of ACL entry created. ACL type entries can only be modified when being configured through the same type command. For example IP-MAC Binding entries can only be modified or deleted through the IP-MAC Binding configurations or commands.

swACLEthernetUnusedRuleEntries.name: swACLEthernetUnusedRuleEntries
swACLEthernetUnusedRuleEntries.description: The number of unused rule entries of this Ethernet profile entry.

swACLEthernetProfileName.name: swACLEthernetProfileName
swACLEthernetProfileName.description: The name of the ACL mask entry unique to the mask list.

swACLIpTable.name: swACLIpTable
swACLIpTable.description: This table contains the ACL mask for IP information. Access profiles will be created on the switch to define which part of the incoming frame's IP layer packet header will be examined by the switch. Masks entered will be combined with the values the switch finds in the specified frame header fields.

swACLIpEntry.name: swACLIpEntry
swACLIpEntry.description: A list of information about the ACL of the IP Layer.

swACLIpProfileID.name: swACLIpProfileID
swACLIpProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL mask entry, which is unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swACLIpUsevlan.name: swACLIpUsevlan
swACLIpUsevlan.description: This object indicates if the IP layer VLAN part is examined or not.

swACLIpIpAddrMaskState.name: swACLIpIpAddrMaskState
swACLIpIpAddrMaskState.description: This object indicates the status of IP address mask. other (1) - Neither source IP address nor destination IP address are masked. dst-ip-addr (2) - Destination IP addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the IP address entry of the table. src-ip-addr (3) - Source IP addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the IP address entry of the table. dst-src-ip-addr (4) - Destination or source IP addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the IP address entry of the table.

swACLIpSrcIpAddrMask.name: swACLIpSrcIpAddrMask
swACLIpSrcIpAddrMask.description: This object specifies the IP address mask for the source IP address.

swACLIpDstIpAddrMask.name: swACLIpDstIpAddrMask
swACLIpDstIpAddrMask.description: This object specifies the IP address mask for the destination IP address.

swACLIpUseDSCP.name: swACLIpUseDSCP
swACLIpUseDSCP.description: This object indicates if the DSCP protocol in the packet header is to be examined or not.

swACLIpUseProtoType.name: swACLIpUseProtoType
swACLIpUseProtoType.description: That object indicates which protocol will be examined.

swACLIpIcmpOption.name: swACLIpIcmpOption
swACLIpIcmpOption.description: This object indicates which fields are defined for ICMP. none (1)- Both fields are null. type (2)- Type field identified. code (3)- Code field identified. type-code (4)- Both ICMP fields identified.

swACLIpIgmpOption.name: swACLIpIgmpOption
swACLIpIgmpOption.description: Indicates if the IGMP options field is identified or not.

swACLIpTcpOption.name: swACLIpTcpOption
swACLIpTcpOption.description: This object indicates the status of the filtered address of TCP. other (1) - Neither source port nor destination port are masked. dst-addr (2) - Packets will be filtered if this destination port is identified in received frames. src-addr (3) - Packets will be filtered if this source port is identified in received frames. dst-src-addr (4) - Packets will be filtered if this destination or source port is identified in received frames.

swACLIpUdpOption.name: swACLIpUdpOption
swACLIpUdpOption.description: This object indicates the status of the filtered address of UDP . other (1) - Neither source port nor destination port are masked. dst-addr (2) - Packets will be filtered if this destination port is identified in received frames. src-addr (3) - Packets will be filtered if this source port is identified in received frames. dst-src-addr (4) - Packets will be filtered if this destination or source port is identified in received frames.

swACLIpTCPorUDPSrcPortMask.name: swACLIpTCPorUDPSrcPortMask
swACLIpTCPorUDPSrcPortMask.description: Specifies a TCP port mask for the source port if swACLIpUseProtoType is TCP Specifies a UDP port mask for the source port if swACLIpUseProtoType is UDP.

swACLIpTCPorUDPDstPortMask.name: swACLIpTCPorUDPDstPortMask
swACLIpTCPorUDPDstPortMask.description: Specifies a TCP port mask for the destination port if swACLIpUseProtoType is TCP Specifies a UDP port mask for the destination port if swACLIpUseProtoType is UDP.

swACLIpTCPFlagBit.name: swACLIpTCPFlagBit
swACLIpTCPFlagBit.description: Specifies a TCP connection flag mask.

swACLIpTCPFlagBitMask.name: swACLIpTCPFlagBitMask
swACLIpTCPFlagBitMask.description: A value which indicates the set of TCP flags that this entity may potentially offer. The value is a sum of flag bits. This sum initially takes the value zero. Then, for each flag, L, is added in the range 1 through 6, for which this node performs transactions where 2^(L-1) is added to the sum. Note that values should be calculated accordingly: Flag functionality 6 urg bit 5 ack bit 4 psh bit 3 rst bit 2 syn bit 1 fin bit For example, if you want to enable urg bit and ack bit, you should set value 48{2^(5-1) + 2^(6-1)}.

swACLIpProtoIDOption.name: swACLIpProtoIDOption
swACLIpProtoIDOption.description: Specifies if the switch will examine each frame's protocol ID field or not.

swACLIpProtoID.name: swACLIpProtoID
swACLIpProtoID.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the IP protocol ID behind the IP header.

swACLIpProtoIDMask.name: swACLIpProtoIDMask
swACLIpProtoIDMask.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the IP protocol ID and the mask options behind the IP header.

swACLIpRowStatus.name: swACLIpRowStatus
swACLIpRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swACLIpOwner.name: swACLIpOwner
swACLIpOwner.description: The owner of the ACL mask entry. The type of ACL entry created. ACL type entries can only be modified when being configured through the same type command. For example, IP-MAC Binding entries can only be modified or deleted through the IP-MAC Binding configurations or commands.

swACLIpUnusedRuleEntries.name: swACLIpUnusedRuleEntries
swACLIpUnusedRuleEntries.description: The number of unused rule entries this IP profile entry.

swACLIpProfileName.name: swACLIpProfileName
swACLIpProfileName.description: The name of the ACL mask entry unique to the mask list.

swACLPktContMaskTable.name: swACLPktContMaskTable
swACLPktContMaskTable.description: This table contains the ACL mask for user-defined information. An access profile will be created on the switch to define which part of each incoming frame's user-defined part of the packet header will be examined by switch. Masks entered will be combined with the values the switch finds in the specified frame header fields.

swACLPktContMaskEntry.name: swACLPktContMaskEntry
swACLPktContMaskEntry.description: A list of information about user-defined ACLs.

swACLPktContMaskProfileID.name: swACLPktContMaskProfileID
swACLPktContMaskProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL mask entry, which is unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swACLPktContMaskOffset0to15.name: swACLPktContMaskOffset0to15
swACLPktContMaskOffset0to15.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the packet content (Offset0to15) and the mask options.

swACLPktContMaskOffset16to31.name: swACLPktContMaskOffset16to31
swACLPktContMaskOffset16to31.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the packet content (Offset16to31) and the mask options.

swACLPktContMaskOffset32to47.name: swACLPktContMaskOffset32to47
swACLPktContMaskOffset32to47.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the packet content (Offset32to47) and the mask options.

swACLPktContMaskOffset48to63.name: swACLPktContMaskOffset48to63
swACLPktContMaskOffset48to63.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the packet content (Offset48to63) and the mask options.

swACLPktContMaskOffset64to79.name: swACLPktContMaskOffset64to79
swACLPktContMaskOffset64to79.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the packet content (Offset64to79) and the mask options.

swACLPktContMaskRowStatus.name: swACLPktContMaskRowStatus
swACLPktContMaskRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swACLPktContMaskOwner.name: swACLPktContMaskOwner
swACLPktContMaskOwner.description: The owner of the ACL mask entry. The type of ACL entry created. ACL type entries can only be modified when being configured through the same type command. For example, IP-MAC Binding entries can only be modified or deleted through the IP-MAC Binding configurations or commands.

swACLPktContMaskUnusedRuleEntries.name: swACLPktContMaskUnusedRuleEntries
swACLPktContMaskUnusedRuleEntries.description: The number of unused rule entries of this IP profile entry.

swACLPktContMaskProfileName.name: swACLPktContMaskProfileName
swACLPktContMaskProfileName.description: The name of the ACL mask entry unique to the mask list.

swACLIpv6MaskTable.name: swACLIpv6MaskTable
swACLIpv6MaskTable.description: This table contains user-defined ACL mask information. An access profile will be created on the switch to define which parts of each incoming frame's IPv6 part of the packet header will be examined by the switch. Masks entered will be combined with the values the switch finds in the specified frame header fields.

swACLIpv6MaskEntry.name: swACLIpv6MaskEntry
swACLIpv6MaskEntry.description: A list of information about user-defined ACLs.

swACLIpv6MaskProfileID.name: swACLIpv6MaskProfileID
swACLIpv6MaskProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL mask entry, which is unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swACLIpv6MaskClass.name: swACLIpv6MaskClass
swACLIpv6MaskClass.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the IPv6 class field and the mask options.

swACLIpv6MaskFlowlabel.name: swACLIpv6MaskFlowlabel
swACLIpv6MaskFlowlabel.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the IPv6 flowlabel field and the mask options.

swACLIpv6IpAddrMaskState.name: swACLIpv6IpAddrMaskState
swACLIpv6IpAddrMaskState.description: This object indicates the status of the IPv6 address mask. other (1) - Neither source IPv6 address nor destination IPv6 address are masked. dst-ipv6-addr (2) - Received frame destination IPv6 address is currently used to be filtered as it meets with the IPv6 address entry of the table. src-ipv6-addr (3) - Received frame source IPv6 address is currently used to be filtered as it meets with the IPv6 address entry of the table. dst-src-ipv6-addr (4) - Received frame destination IPv6 address or source IPv6 address is currently used to be filtered as it meets with the IPv6 address entry of the table.

swACLIpv6MaskSrcIpv6Mask.name: swACLIpv6MaskSrcIpv6Mask
swACLIpv6MaskSrcIpv6Mask.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the Source IPv6 address and the mask options. This should be a 16 byte octet string.

swACLIpv6MaskDstIpv6Mask.name: swACLIpv6MaskDstIpv6Mask
swACLIpv6MaskDstIpv6Mask.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the Destination IPv6 address and the mask options. This should be a 16 byte octet string.

swACLIpv6MaskRowStatus.name: swACLIpv6MaskRowStatus
swACLIpv6MaskRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swACLIpv6MaskOwner.name: swACLIpv6MaskOwner
swACLIpv6MaskOwner.description: The owner of the ACL mask entry. The type of ACL entry created. ACL type entries can only be modified when being configured through the same type command. For example, IP-MAC Binding entries can only be modified or deleted through the IP-MAC Binding configurations or commands.

swACLIpv6MaskUnusedRuleEntries.name: swACLIpv6MaskUnusedRuleEntries
swACLIpv6MaskUnusedRuleEntries.description: The number of unused rule entries of this IP profile entry.

swACLIpv6MaskProfileName.name: swACLIpv6MaskProfileName
swACLIpv6MaskProfileName.description: The name of the ACL mask entry unique to the mask list.

swACLIpv6MaskUseProtoType.name: swACLIpv6MaskUseProtoType
swACLIpv6MaskUseProtoType.description: That object indicates which protocol will be examined.

swACLIpv6MaskTcpOption.name: swACLIpv6MaskTcpOption
swACLIpv6MaskTcpOption.description: This object indicates the status of the filtered address of TCP. other (1) - Neither source port nor destination port are masked. dst-addr (2) - Packets will be filtered if this destination port is identified in received frames. src-addr (3) - Packets will be filtered if this source port is identified in received frames. dst-src-addr (4) - Packets will be filtered if this destination or source port is identified in received frames.

swACLIpv6MaskUdpOption.name: swACLIpv6MaskUdpOption
swACLIpv6MaskUdpOption.description: This object indicates the status of the filtered address of UDP. other (1) - Neither source port nor destination port is masked. dst-addr (2) - Packets will be filtered if this destination port is identified in received frames. src-addr (3) - Packets will be filtered if this source port is identified in received frames. dst-src-addr (4) - Packets will be filtered if this destination or source port is identified in received frames.

swACLIpv6MaskTCPorUDPSrcPortMask.name: swACLIpv6MaskTCPorUDPSrcPortMask
swACLIpv6MaskTCPorUDPSrcPortMask.description: Specifies a TCP port mask for the source port if swACLIpv6MaskUseProtoType is TCP Specifies a UDP port mask for the source port if swACLIpv6MaskUseProtoType is UDP.

swACLIpv6MaskTCPorUDPDstPortMask.name: swACLIpv6MaskTCPorUDPDstPortMask
swACLIpv6MaskTCPorUDPDstPortMask.description: Specifies a TCP port mask for the destination port if swACLIpv6MaskUseProtoType is TCP Specifies a UDP port mask for the destination port if swACLIpv6MaskUseProtoType is UDP.

swACLMaskDelAllState.name: swACLMaskDelAllState
swACLMaskDelAllState.description: Used to delete all ACL masks.

swIBPACLEthernetTable.name: swIBPACLEthernetTable
swIBPACLEthernetTable.description: This table contains IP-MAC-Binding ACL mask Ethernet information. Access profiles will be created on the switch by row creation and to define which parts of each incoming frame's layer 2 header part the switch will examine. Masks can be entered that will be combined with the values the switch finds in the specified frame header fields.

swIBPACLEthernetEntry.name: swIBPACLEthernetEntry
swIBPACLEthernetEntry.description: A list of information about the Ethernet ACL.

swIBPACLEthernetProfileID.name: swIBPACLEthernetProfileID
swIBPACLEthernetProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL mask entry, unique in the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swIBPACLEthernetUseEthernetType.name: swIBPACLEthernetUseEthernetType
swIBPACLEthernetUseEthernetType.description: Specifies if the switch will examine the Ethernet type value in each frame's header or not.

swIBPACLIpTable.name: swIBPACLIpTable
swIBPACLIpTable.description: This table contains IP-MAC-Binding IP ACL mask information. Access profiles will be created on the switch by row creation and to define which parts of each incoming frame's IP layer part of the header the switch will examine. Masks can be entered that will be combined with the values the switch finds in the specified frame header fields.

swIBPACLIpEntry.name: swIBPACLIpEntry
swIBPACLIpEntry.description: A list of information about the IP layer of the ACL.

swIBPACLIpProfileID.name: swIBPACLIpProfileID
swIBPACLIpProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL mask entry, unique in the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swIBPACLIpSrcMacAddrMask.name: swIBPACLIpSrcMacAddrMask
swIBPACLIpSrcMacAddrMask.description: This object specifies the MAC address mask for the source MAC address.

swIBPACLIpSrcIpAddrMask.name: swIBPACLIpSrcIpAddrMask
swIBPACLIpSrcIpAddrMask.description: This object specifies IP address masks for the source IP address.

swACLPktContMaskOptionTable.name: swACLPktContMaskOptionTable
swACLPktContMaskOptionTable.description: This table contains the ACL mask for user-defined option information. An access profile will be created on the switch to define which part of each incoming frame's user-defined part of the packet header will be examined by switch. Masks entered will be combined with the values the switch finds in the specified frame header fields.

swACLPktContMaskOptionEntry.name: swACLPktContMaskOptionEntry
swACLPktContMaskOptionEntry.description: A list of information about the user-defined ACL.

swACLPktContMaskOptionProfileID.name: swACLPktContMaskOptionProfileID
swACLPktContMaskOptionProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL mask entry, unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk1OffsetValue.name: swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk1OffsetValue
swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk1OffsetValue.description: Specifies the frame content offset of chunk1.

swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk1Mask.name: swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk1Mask
swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk1Mask.description: Specifies the frame content mask of chunk1.

swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk2OffsetValue.name: swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk2OffsetValue
swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk2OffsetValue.description: Specifies the frame content offset of chunk2.

swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk2Mask.name: swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk2Mask
swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk2Mask.description: Specifies the frame content mask of chunk2.

swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk3OffsetValue.name: swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk3OffsetValue
swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk3OffsetValue.description: Specifies the frame content offset of chunk3.

swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk3Mask.name: swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk3Mask
swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk3Mask.description: Specifies the frame content mask of chunk3.

swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk4OffsetValue.name: swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk4OffsetValue
swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk4OffsetValue.description: Specifies the frame content offset of chunk4.

swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk4Mask.name: swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk4Mask
swACLPktContMaskOffsetChunk4Mask.description: Specifies the frame content mask of chunk4.

swACLPktContMaskOptionRowStatus.name: swACLPktContMaskOptionRowStatus
swACLPktContMaskOptionRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swACLPktContMaskOptionOwner.name: swACLPktContMaskOptionOwner
swACLPktContMaskOptionOwner.description: The owner of the ACL mask entry. The type of ACL entry created. ACL type entries can only be modified when being configured through the same type command. For example, IP-MAC Binding entries can only be modified or deleted through the IP-MAC Binding configurations or commands.

swACLPktContMaskOptionUnusedRuleEntries.name: swACLPktContMaskOptionUnusedRuleEntries
swACLPktContMaskOptionUnusedRuleEntries.description: The number of unused rule entries of this IP profile entry.

swACLPktContMaskOptionProfileName.name: swACLPktContMaskOptionProfileName
swACLPktContMaskOptionProfileName.description: The name of the ACL mask entry unique to the mask list.

swACLEtherRuleTable.name: swACLEtherRuleTable
swACLEtherRuleTable.description: This table contains Ethernet ACL information.

swACLEtherRuleEntry.name: swACLEtherRuleEntry
swACLEtherRuleEntry.description: A list of information about the ACL rule of the layer 2 part of each packet.

swACLEtherRuleProfileID.name: swACLEtherRuleProfileID
swACLEtherRuleProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL rule entry, which is unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swACLEtherRuleAccessID.name: swACLEtherRuleAccessID
swACLEtherRuleAccessID.description: The ID of the the ACL rule entry relates to the swACLEtherRuleProfileID. When row creation is set to 0, assignment of an Access ID for ports is automatic and the swACLEtherRulePort creates Rule entries for the swACLEtherRulePort accordingly. When set from 1 to 65535, an access ID will be created for the swACLEtherRulePort. The swACLEtherRulePort must be set to one port only otherwise the row creation will fail.

swACLEtherRuleVlan.name: swACLEtherRuleVlan
swACLEtherRuleVlan.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply to this VLAN only.

swACLEtherRuleSrcMacAddress.name: swACLEtherRuleSrcMacAddress
swACLEtherRuleSrcMacAddress.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply to only packets with this source MAC address.

swACLEtherRuleDstMacAddress.name: swACLEtherRuleDstMacAddress
swACLEtherRuleDstMacAddress.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply to only packets with this destination MAC address.

swACLEtherRule8021P.name: swACLEtherRule8021P
swACLEtherRule8021P.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply only to packets with this 802.1p priority value. A value of -1 indicates that this node is not actively used.

swACLEtherRuleEtherType.name: swACLEtherRuleEtherType
swACLEtherRuleEtherType.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply only to packets with this hexadecimal 802.1Q Ethernet type value in the packet header.

swACLEtherRuleEnablePriority.name: swACLEtherRuleEnablePriority
swACLEtherRuleEnablePriority.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply only to packets with priority value.

swACLEtherRulePriority.name: swACLEtherRulePriority
swACLEtherRulePriority.description: Specifies that the priority will be changed in packets while the swACLEtherRuleEnablePriority is enabled .

swACLEtherRuleReplacePriority.name: swACLEtherRuleReplacePriority
swACLEtherRuleReplacePriority.description: Specifies if the switch will change priorities of packets that match the access profile 802.1p priority tag field or not .

swACLEtherRuleEnableReplaceDscp.name: swACLEtherRuleEnableReplaceDscp
swACLEtherRuleEnableReplaceDscp.description: Specifies if the switch will change priorities of packets that match the access profile DSCP field or not. Replace DSCP and replace ToS precedence can not both be supported.

swACLEtherRuleRepDscp.name: swACLEtherRuleRepDscp
swACLEtherRuleRepDscp.description: Specifies a value to be written to the DSCP field of an incoming packet that meets the criteria specified in the first part of the command. This value will over-write the value in the DSCP field of the packet.

swACLEtherRulePermit.name: swACLEtherRulePermit
swACLEtherRulePermit.description: This object indicates if the result of the packet examination is 'permit' or 'deny'. The default is 'permit'. permit - Specifies that packets that match the access profile are permitted to be forwarded by the switch. deny - Specifies that packets that match the access profile are not permitted to be forwarded by the switch and will be filtered.

swACLEtherRulePort.name: swACLEtherRulePort
swACLEtherRulePort.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to port(s). This object and swACLEtherRuleVID can not be set together.

swACLEtherRuleRowStatus.name: swACLEtherRuleRowStatus
swACLEtherRuleRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swACLEtherRuleOwner.name: swACLEtherRuleOwner
swACLEtherRuleOwner.description: The owner of the ACL rule entry. Only owners can modify this entry.

swACLEtherRuleRxRate.name: swACLEtherRuleRxRate
swACLEtherRuleRxRate.description: Specifies the rx rate, 0 denotes no_limit. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swACLEtherRuleEnableReplaceTosPrecedence.name: swACLEtherRuleEnableReplaceTosPrecedence
swACLEtherRuleEnableReplaceTosPrecedence.description: Specifies if the switch will change priorities of packets that match the access profile ToS precedence field or not. Replace DSCP and replace ToS precedence can not both be supported.

swACLEtherRuleRepTosPrecedence.name: swACLEtherRuleRepTosPrecedence
swACLEtherRuleRepTosPrecedence.description: Specifies a value to be written to the ToS precedence field of an incoming packet that meets the criteria specified in the first part of the command. This value will over-write the value in the ToS precedence field of the packet.

swACLEtherRuleVID.name: swACLEtherRuleVID
swACLEtherRuleVID.description: Specifies this rule only applies to the specified VLAN. There are two conditions: 1.only the portlist that belongs to this VLAN will be included; 2.packets must belong to this VLAN. This object and swACLEtherRulePort can not be set together. When you set swACLEtherRulePort, the value of this object will automatically change to 0. And this object can not be set to 0.

swACLIpRuleProfileID.name: swACLIpRuleProfileID
swACLIpRuleProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL mask entry, which is unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swACLIpRuleAccessID.name: swACLIpRuleAccessID
swACLIpRuleAccessID.description: The ID of the ACL rule entry relates to swACLIPRuleProfileID. Row creation set to 0 indicates automatic assignment of the Access ID for the ports in the swACLIpRulePort to create Rule entries for swACLIpRulePort accordingly. Set to 1-65535 causes creation of an access ID for the swACLIpRulePort. The swACLIpRulePort must be set to one port only otherwise the row creation will fail.

swACLIpRuleVlan.name: swACLIpRuleVlan
swACLIpRuleVlan.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to this VLAN.

swACLIpRuleDscp.name: swACLIpRuleDscp
swACLIpRuleDscp.description: Specifies the value of DSCP. The value can be configured from 0 to 63. A value of -1 indicates that this node is not actively used.

swACLIpRuleProtocol.name: swACLIpRuleProtocol
swACLIpRuleProtocol.description: Specifies the IP protocol. For some older chips, this object can not be set. When getting this object, it always returns the type which has been configured in swACLIpEntry. For some newer chips, this object can only set the type which has been configured in swACLIpEntry. The default value is none (1).

swACLIpRuleType.name: swACLIpRuleType
swACLIpRuleType.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the value of ICMP type traffic. A value of -1 denotes that this object is not active.

swACLIpRuleCode.name: swACLIpRuleCode
swACLIpRuleCode.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the value of ICMP code traffic. A value of -1 denotes that this object is not active.

swACLIpRuleSrcPort.name: swACLIpRuleSrcPort
swACLIpRuleSrcPort.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the range of the TCP/UDP source ports. A value of -1 indicates that this node is not actively used.

swACLIpRuleDstPort.name: swACLIpRuleDstPort
swACLIpRuleDstPort.description: Specifies the TCP/UDP destination port range. A value of -1 indicates that this node is not actively used.

swACLIpRuleFlagBits.name: swACLIpRuleFlagBits
swACLIpRuleFlagBits.description: A value which indicates the set of TCP flags that this entity may potentially offer. The value is a sum of flag bits. This sum initially takes the value zero. Then, for each flag, L is added in the range 1 through 6, for which this node performs transactions, where 2^(L - 1) is added to the sum. Note that values should be calculated accordingly: Flag functionality 6 urg bit 5 ack bit 4 psh bit 3 rst bit 2 syn bit 1 fin bit For example, it you want to enable urg bit and ack bit, you should set value 48{2^(5-1) + 2^(6-1)}.

swACLIpRuleProtoID.name: swACLIpRuleProtoID
swACLIpRuleProtoID.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the value of IP protocol ID traffic. A value of -1 indicates that this node is not actively used.

swACLIpRuleUserMask.name: swACLIpRuleUserMask
swACLIpRuleUserMask.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the IP protocol ID and the range of options behind the IP header.

swACLIpRuleEnablePriority.name: swACLIpRuleEnablePriority
swACLIpRuleEnablePriority.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply only to packets with this priority value.

swACLIpRulePriority.name: swACLIpRulePriority
swACLIpRulePriority.description: Specifies the priority will change in packets while the swACLIpRuleEnablePriority is enabled.

swACLIpRuleReplacePriority.name: swACLIpRuleReplacePriority
swACLIpRuleReplacePriority.description: Specifies whether the packets that match the access profile will change the 802.1p priority tag field by the switch or not.

swACLIpRuleEnableReplaceDscp.name: swACLIpRuleEnableReplaceDscp
swACLIpRuleEnableReplaceDscp.description: Specifies if the switch will change priorities of packets that match the access profile DSCP field or not. Replace DSCP and replace ToS precedence can not both be supported.

swACLIpRuleRepDscp.name: swACLIpRuleRepDscp
swACLIpRuleRepDscp.description: Specifies a value to be written to the DSCP field of an incoming packet that meets the criteria specified in the first part of the command. This value will over-write the value in the DSCP field of the packet.

swACLIpRulePermit.name: swACLIpRulePermit
swACLIpRulePermit.description: This object indicates if the result of the packet examination is to 'permit' or 'deny'. The default is 'permit'. permit - Specifies that packets that match the access profile are permitted to be forwarded by the switch. deny - Specifies that packets that match the access profile are not permitted to be forwarded by the switch and will be filtered.

swACLIpRulePort.name: swACLIpRulePort
swACLIpRulePort.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to port(s). This object and swACLIpRuleVID can not be set together.

swACLIpRuleRowStatus.name: swACLIpRuleRowStatus
swACLIpRuleRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swACLIpRuleOwner.name: swACLIpRuleOwner
swACLIpRuleOwner.description: The owner of the ACL rule entry. Only owners can modify this entry.

swACLIpRuleRxRate.name: swACLIpRuleRxRate
swACLIpRuleRxRate.description: Specifies the rx-rate, 0 denotes no_limit. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swACLIpRuleEnableReplaceTosPrecedence.name: swACLIpRuleEnableReplaceTosPrecedence
swACLIpRuleEnableReplaceTosPrecedence.description: Specifies if the switch will change priorities of packets that match the access profile ToS precedence field or not. Replace DSCP and replace ToS precedence can not both be supported.

swACLIpRuleRepTosPrecedence.name: swACLIpRuleRepTosPrecedence
swACLIpRuleRepTosPrecedence.description: Specifies a value to be written to the ToS precedence field of an incoming packet that meets the criteria specified in the first part of the command. This value will over-write the value in the ToS precedence field of the packet.

swACLIpRuleVID.name: swACLIpRuleVID
swACLIpRuleVID.description: Specifies this rule only applies to the specified VLAN. There are two conditions: 1.only the portlist that belongs to this VLAN will be included; 2.packets must belong to this VLAN. This object and swACLIpRulePort can not be set together. When you set swACLIpRulePort, the value of this object will automatically change to 0. And this object can not be set 0.

swACLIpv6RuleTable.name: swACLIpv6RuleTable
swACLIpv6RuleTable.description: This table contains the IPv6 ACL rule information.

swACLIpv6RuleEntry.name: swACLIpv6RuleEntry
swACLIpv6RuleEntry.description: A list of information about ACL rules regarding the IPv6 part of each packet.

swACLIpv6RuleProfileID.name: swACLIpv6RuleProfileID
swACLIpv6RuleProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL mask entry, which is unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swACLIpv6RuleAccessID.name: swACLIpv6RuleAccessID
swACLIpv6RuleAccessID.description: The ID of the ACL rule entry relates to swACLIpv6RuleProfileID. When row creation is set to 0, this indicates the access ID will be assigned automatically for the ports in the swACLIpv6RulePort to create rule entries for swACLIpv6RulePort accordingly. Set to 1-65535 indicates creation of an access ID for the swACLIpv6RulePort. The swACLIpv6RulePort must be set to one port only, otherwise the row creation will fail.

swACLIpv6RuleClass.name: swACLIpv6RuleClass
swACLIpv6RuleClass.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the IPv6 class field.

swACLIpv6RuleFlowlabel.name: swACLIpv6RuleFlowlabel
swACLIpv6RuleFlowlabel.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the IPv6 flow label field.

swACLIpv6RuleSrcIpv6Addr.name: swACLIpv6RuleSrcIpv6Addr
swACLIpv6RuleSrcIpv6Addr.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the source IPv6 address. This should be a 16 byte octet string.

swACLIpv6RuleDstIpv6Addr.name: swACLIpv6RuleDstIpv6Addr
swACLIpv6RuleDstIpv6Addr.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the destination IPv6 address. This should be a 16 byte octet string.

swACLIpv6RuleEnablePriority.name: swACLIpv6RuleEnablePriority
swACLIpv6RuleEnablePriority.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply only to packets with priority value.

swACLIpv6RulePriority.name: swACLIpv6RulePriority
swACLIpv6RulePriority.description: Specifies the priority will change in packets while the swACLIpv6RuleReplacePriority is enabled.

swACLIpv6RuleReplacePriority.name: swACLIpv6RuleReplacePriority
swACLIpv6RuleReplacePriority.description: Specifies if the switch will change priorities of packets that match the access profile 802.1p priority tag or not.

swACLIpv6RulePermit.name: swACLIpv6RulePermit
swACLIpv6RulePermit.description: This object indicates if the result of packet examination is to 'permit' or 'deny'. The default is 'permit'. permit - Specifies that packets that match the access profile are permitted to be forwarded by the switch. deny - Specifies that packets that match the access profile are not permitted to be forwarded by the switch and will be filtered. mirror - Specifies the packets that match the access profile are copied to the mirror port. Note: The ACL mirror function will work after mirror has been enabled and the mirror port has been configured.

swACLIpv6RulePort.name: swACLIpv6RulePort
swACLIpv6RulePort.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply only to port(s). This object and swACLIpv6RuleVID can not be set together.

swACLIpv6RuleRowStatus.name: swACLIpv6RuleRowStatus
swACLIpv6RuleRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swACLIpv6RuleOwner.name: swACLIpv6RuleOwner
swACLIpv6RuleOwner.description: The owner of the ACL rule entry. Only owners can modify this entry.

swACLIpv6RuleRxRate.name: swACLIpv6RuleRxRate
swACLIpv6RuleRxRate.description: Specifies the rx-rate, 0 denotes no_limit. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swACLIpv6RuleEnableReplaceDscp.name: swACLIpv6RuleEnableReplaceDscp
swACLIpv6RuleEnableReplaceDscp.description: Specifies if the switch will change priorities of packets that match the access profile DSCP field or not. Replace DSCP and replace ToS precedence can not both be supported.

swACLIpv6RuleRepDscp.name: swACLIpv6RuleRepDscp
swACLIpv6RuleRepDscp.description: Specifies a value to be written to the DSCP field of an incoming packet that meets the criteria specified in the first part of the command. This value will over-write the value in the DSCP field of the packet.

swACLIpv6RuleEnableReplaceTosPrecedence.name: swACLIpv6RuleEnableReplaceTosPrecedence
swACLIpv6RuleEnableReplaceTosPrecedence.description: Specifies if the switch will change priorities of packets that match the access profile ToS precedence field or not. Replace DSCP and replace ToS precedence can not both be supported.

swACLIpv6RuleRepTosPrecedence.name: swACLIpv6RuleRepTosPrecedence
swACLIpv6RuleRepTosPrecedence.description: Specifies a value to be written to the ToS precedence field of an incoming packet that meets the criteria specified in the first part of the command. This value will over-write the value in the ToS precedence field of the packet.

swACLIpv6RuleVID.name: swACLIpv6RuleVID
swACLIpv6RuleVID.description: Specifies this rule only applies to the specified VLAN. There are two conditions: 1.only the portlist that belongs to this VLAN will be included; 2.packets must belong to this VLAN. This object and swACLIpv6RulePort can not be set together. When you set swACLIpv6RulePort, the value of this object will automatically change to 0. And this object can not be set 0.

swACLIpv6RuleProtocol.name: swACLIpv6RuleProtocol
swACLIpv6RuleProtocol.description: Specifies the IPv6 protocol. For some older chips, this object can not be set. When getting this object, it always returns the type which has been configured in swACLIpv6Entry. For some newer chips, this object can only set the type which has been configured in swACLIpv6Entry. The default value is none (1).

swACLIpv6RuleSrcPort.name: swACLIpv6RuleSrcPort
swACLIpv6RuleSrcPort.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the range of the TCP/UDP source ports.

swACLIpv6RuleDstPort.name: swACLIpv6RuleDstPort
swACLIpv6RuleDstPort.description: Specifies the TCP/UDP destination ports range.

swIBPACLEtherRuleTable.name: swIBPACLEtherRuleTable
swIBPACLEtherRuleTable.description: This table contains IP-MAC-Binding Ethernet ACL Rule information.

swIBPACLEtherRuleEntry.name: swIBPACLEtherRuleEntry
swIBPACLEtherRuleEntry.description: A list of information about the ACL rule of the layer 2 part of each packet.

swIBPACLEtherRuleProfileID.name: swIBPACLEtherRuleProfileID
swIBPACLEtherRuleProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL mask entry, unique in the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swIBPACLEtherRuleAccessID.name: swIBPACLEtherRuleAccessID
swIBPACLEtherRuleAccessID.description: The ID of the ACL rule entry in relation to swACLEtherRuleProfileID. When row creation is set to 0, this indicates automatically assigning an Access for the ports in the swACLEtherRulePort to create rule entries for swACLEtherRulePort accordingly. Set to 1-65535 indicates to create the exact access ID for the swACLEtherRulePort and the swACLEtherRulePort must set one port only, otherwise the row creation will fail.

swIBPACLEtherRuleEtherType.name: swIBPACLEtherRuleEtherType
swIBPACLEtherRuleEtherType.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply only to packets with this 802.1Q Ethernet type value in the packet header.

swIBPACLEtherRulePermit.name: swIBPACLEtherRulePermit
swIBPACLEtherRulePermit.description: This object indicates if the result of the examination is 'permit' or 'deny'. The default is 'permit' (1). permit - Specifies that packets that match the access profile are permitted to be forwarded by the switch. deny - Specifies that packets that match the access profile are not permitted to be forwarded by the switch and will be filtered.

swIBPACLEtherRulePort.name: swIBPACLEtherRulePort
swIBPACLEtherRulePort.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to port(s).

swIBPACLIpRuleProfileID.name: swIBPACLIpRuleProfileID
swIBPACLIpRuleProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL mask entry, unique in the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swIBPACLIpRuleAccessID.name: swIBPACLIpRuleAccessID
swIBPACLIpRuleAccessID.description: The ID of the ACL rule entry in relation to swACLIPRuleProfileID. When the row creation is set to 0, this indicates assigning an access ID automatically for the ports in the swACLIpRulePort to create rule entries for swACLIpRulePort accordingly. Set to 1-65535 indicates to create the exact access ID for the swACLIpRulePort and the swACLIpRulePort must be set for one port only, otherwise the row creation will fail.

swIBPACLIpRuleSrcMacAddress.name: swIBPACLIpRuleSrcMacAddress
swIBPACLIpRuleSrcMacAddress.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply to only packets with this source MAC address.

swIBPACLIpRulePermit.name: swIBPACLIpRulePermit
swIBPACLIpRulePermit.description: This object indicates if the result of the examination is 'permit' or 'deny'; the default is 'permit' (1) permit - Specifies that packets that match the access profile are permitted to be forwarded by the switch. deny - Specifies that packets that match the access profile are not permitted to be forwarded by the switch and will be filtered.

swIBPACLIpRulePort.name: swIBPACLIpRulePort
swIBPACLIpRulePort.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to port(s).

swACLCounterTable.name: swACLCounterTable
swACLCounterTable.description: This table maintains counter information associated with a specific rule in the ACL rule table. Please refer to the swACLEtherRuleTable, swACLIpRuleTable, swACLIpv6RuleTable and swACLPktContRuleTable for detailed ACL rule information.

swACLCounterEntry.name: swACLCounterEntry
swACLCounterEntry.description: The entry maintains counter information associated with the ACL rule table.

swACLCounterProfileID.name: swACLCounterProfileID
swACLCounterProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL mask entry, which is unique in the mask list.

swACLCounterAccessID.name: swACLCounterAccessID
swACLCounterAccessID.description: The ID of the ACL rule entry as related to the swACLCounterProfileID.

swACLCounterState.name: swACLCounterState
swACLCounterState.description: Specifies whether the counter feature will be enabled/disabled. 1. This is optional. The default is disable. 2. If the rule is not bound with flow_meter, then all packets that match will be counted. If the rule is bound with flow_meter, then the 'counter' will be overridden.

swACLCounterGreenCounter.name: swACLCounterGreenCounter
swACLCounterGreenCounter.description: The number of matched green packets.

swACLCounterYellowCounter.name: swACLCounterYellowCounter
swACLCounterYellowCounter.description: The number of matched yellow packets.

swACLCounterRedCounter.name: swACLCounterRedCounter
swACLCounterRedCounter.description: The number of matched red packets.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetTable.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetTable
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetTable.description: This table is used to configure ACL user defined packet content rules for devices that support limited selection of packet content.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetEntry.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetEntry
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetEntry.description: A list which contains information on the ACL rules for user-defined parts of a packet.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetProfileID.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetProfileID
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetProfileID.description: The ID of ACL mask entry, which is unique to the mask list.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetAccessID.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetAccessID
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetAccessID.description: The ID of ACL rule entry related to swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetProfileID.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex1.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex1
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex1.description: Specifies the first offset will apply in getting the mask for this rule.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask1.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask1
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask1.description: Display the mask for this rule. This mask corresponds to swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex1 and swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData1.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData1.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData1
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData1.description: Specifies the data for this rule. This rule relates to swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex1 and swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask1.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex2.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex2
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex2.description: Specifies the second offset will apply in getting the mask for this rule.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask2.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask2
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask2.description: Display the mask for this rule. This mask corresponds to swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex2 and swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData2.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData2.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData2
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData2.description: Specifies the data for this rule. This rule relates to swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex2 and swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask2.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex3.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex3
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex3.description: Specifies the third offset will apply in getting the mask for this rule.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask3.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask3
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask3.description: Display the mask for this rule. This mask corresponds to swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex3 and swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData3.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData3.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData3
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData3.description: Specifies the data for this rule. This rule relates to swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex3 and swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask3.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex4.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex4
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex4.description: Specifies the fourth offset will apply in getting the mask for this rule.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask4.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask4
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask4.description: Display the mask for this rule. This mask corresponds to swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex4 and swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData4.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData4.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData4
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData4.description: Specifies the data for this rule. This rule relates to swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex4 and swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask4.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex5.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex5
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex5.description: Specifies the fifth offset will apply in getting the mask for this rule.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask5.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask5
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask5.description: Display the mask for this rule. This mask corresponds to swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex5 and swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData5.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData5.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData5
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetData5.description: Specifies the data for this rule. This rule relates to swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetOffsetIndex5 and swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetMask5.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetEnablePriority.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetEnablePriority
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetEnablePriority.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply only to packets with this priority value.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetPriority.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetPriority
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetPriority.description: Specifies the priority will change to the packets.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetReplacePriority.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetReplacePriority
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetReplacePriority.description: Specifies if the switch will change priorities of packets that match the access profile 802.1p priority tag or not .

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetRxRate.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetRxRate
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetRxRate.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply an RX rate. 0 denotes no limit.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetPermit.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetPermit
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetPermit.description: This object indicates the result of the packet examination is to permit or deny. The default is permit. permit - Specifies that packets that match the access profile are permitted to be forwarded by the switch. deny - Specifies that packets that do not match the access profile are not permitted to be forwarded by the switch and will be filtered.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetPort.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetPort
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetPort.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply only to port(s).

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetRowStatus.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetRowStatus
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetReplacePriority.name: swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetReplacePriorityWith
swACLPktContRuleVarOffsetReplacePriority.description: The value of this node will be used to replace the 802.1p priority tag of the packet that matched the access profile.

swCpuAclEthernetTable.name: swCpuAclEthernetTable
swCpuAclEthernetTable.description: This table contains software ACL mask Ethernet information. Access profiles will be created on the switch to define which part of each incoming frame's layer 2 header will be examined by the switch. Masks entered will be combined with the values the switch finds in the specified frame header fields.

swCpuAclEthernetEntry.name: swCpuAclEthernetEntry
swCpuAclEthernetEntry.description: A list of information about Ethernet ACL masks.

swCpuAclEthernetProfileID.name: swCpuAclEthernetProfileID
swCpuAclEthernetProfileID.description: The ID of the software ACL mask entry, which is unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swCpuAclEthernetUsevlan.name: swCpuAclEthernetUsevlan
swCpuAclEthernetUsevlan.description: Specifies that the switch will examine the VLAN part of each packet header.

swCpuAclEthernetMacAddrMaskState.name: swCpuAclEthernetMacAddrMaskState
swCpuAclEthernetMacAddrMaskState.description: This object indicates the status of the MAC address mask. other (1) - Neither source MAC addresses nor destination MAC addresses are masked. dst-mac-addr (2) - Destination MAC addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the MAC address entry of the table. src-mac-addr (3) - Source MAC address within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the MAC address entry of the table. dst-src-mac-addr (4) - Source or destination MAC addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the MAC address entry of this table.

swCpuAclEthernetSrcMacAddrMask.name: swCpuAclEthernetSrcMacAddrMask
swCpuAclEthernetSrcMacAddrMask.description: This object specifies the MAC address mask for the source MAC address.

swCpuAclEthernetDstMacAddrMask.name: swCpuAclEthernetDstMacAddrMask
swCpuAclEthernetDstMacAddrMask.description: This object specifies the MAC address mask for the destination MAC address.

swCpuAclEthernetUse8021p.name: swCpuAclEthernetUse8021p
swCpuAclEthernetUse8021p.description: Specifies if the switch will examine the 802.1p priority value in the frame's header or not.

swCpuAclEthernetUseEthernetType.name: swCpuAclEthernetUseEthernetType
swCpuAclEthernetUseEthernetType.description: Specifies if the switch will examine the Ethernet type value in each frame's header or not.

swCpuAclEthernetRowStatus.name: swCpuAclEthernetRowStatus
swCpuAclEthernetRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swCpuAclIpTable.name: swCpuAclIpTable
swCpuAclIpTable.description: This table contains software ACL mask IP information. Access profiles will be created on the switch to define which parts of each incoming frame's IP layer 2 header will be examined by the switch. Masks entered will be combined with the values the switch finds in the specified frame header fields.

swCpuAclIpEntry.name: swCpuAclIpEntry
swCpuAclIpEntry.description: A list of information about the software ACL of the IP Layer.

swCpuAclIpProfileID.name: swCpuAclIpProfileID
swCpuAclIpProfileID.description: The ID of the software ACL mask entry, which is unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swCpuAclIpUsevlan.name: swCpuAclIpUsevlan
swCpuAclIpUsevlan.description: This object indicates if the IP layer VLAN part is examined or not.

swCpuAclIpIpAddrMaskState.name: swCpuAclIpIpAddrMaskState
swCpuAclIpIpAddrMaskState.description: This object indicates the status of IP address mask. other (1) - Neither source IP addresses nor destination IP address are masked. dst-ip-addr (2) - Destination IP addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the IP address entry of this table. src-ip-addr (3) - Source IP addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the IP address entry of this table. dst-src-ip-addr (4) - Destination or source IP addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the IP address entry of the table.

swCpuAclIpSrcIpAddrMask.name: swCpuAclIpSrcIpAddrMask
swCpuAclIpSrcIpAddrMask.description: This object specifies the IP address mask for the source IP address.

swCpuAclIpDstIpAddrMask.name: swCpuAclIpDstIpAddrMask
swCpuAclIpDstIpAddrMask.description: This object specifies the IP address mask for the destination IP address.

swCpuAclIpUseDSCP.name: swCpuAclIpUseDSCP
swCpuAclIpUseDSCP.description: This object indicates if the DSCP protocol in the packet header is to be examined or not.

swCpuAclIpUseProtoType.name: swCpuAclIpUseProtoType
swCpuAclIpUseProtoType.description: This object indicates which protocol will be examined.

swCpuAclIpIcmpOption.name: swCpuAclIpIcmpOption
swCpuAclIpIcmpOption.description: This object indicates which fields are identified for ICMP. none (1)- Both fields are null. type (2)- Type field identified. code (3)- Code field identified. type-code (4)- Both ICMP fields identified.

swCpuAclIpIgmpOption.name: swCpuAclIpIgmpOption
swCpuAclIpIgmpOption.description: This object indicates if the IGMP options field is identified or not.

swCpuAclIpTcpOption.name: swCpuAclIpTcpOption
swCpuAclIpTcpOption.description: This object indicates the status of filtered addresses of TCP. other (1) - Neither source port nor destination port are masked. dst-addr (2) - Packets will be filtered if this destination port is identified in received frames. src-addr (3) - Packets will be filtered if this source port is identified in received frames. dst-src-addr (4) - Packets will be filtered is this destination or source port is identified in received frames.

swCpuAclIpUdpOption.name: swCpuAclIpUdpOption
swCpuAclIpUdpOption.description: This object indicates the status of filtered addresses of UDP. other (1) - Neither source port nor destination port are masked. dst-addr (2) - Packets will be filtered if this destination port is identified in received frames. src-addr (3) - Packets will be filtered if this source port is identified in received frames. dst-src-addr (4) - Packets will be filtered if this destination or source port is identified in received frames.

swCpuAclIpTCPorUDPSrcPortMask.name: swCpuAclIpTCPorUDPSrcPortMask
swCpuAclIpTCPorUDPSrcPortMask.description: Specifies a TCP port mask for the source port if swCpuAclIpUseProtoType is TCP. Specifies a UDP port mask for the source port if swCpuAclIpUseProtoType is UDP.

swCpuAclIpTCPorUDPDstPortMask.name: swCpuAclIpTCPorUDPDstPortMask
swCpuAclIpTCPorUDPDstPortMask.description: Specifies a TCP port mask for the destination port if swCpuAclIpUseProtoType is TCP. Specifies a UDP port mask for the destination port if swCpuAclIpUseProtoType is UDP.

swCpuAclIpTCPFlagBit.name: swCpuAclIpTCPFlagBit
swCpuAclIpTCPFlagBit.description: Specifies a TCP connection flag mask.

swCpuAclIpTCPFlagBitMask.name: swCpuAclIpTCPFlagBitMask
swCpuAclIpTCPFlagBitMask.description: A value which indicates the set of TCP flags that this entity may potentially offer. The value is a sum of flag bits. This sum initially takes the value zero. Then, for each flag, L is added in the range 1 through 6, for which this node performs transactions where 2^(L - 1) is added to the sum. Note that values should be calculated accordingly: Flag functionality 6 urg bit 5 ack bit 4 psh bit 3 rst bit 2 syn bit 1 fin bit For example, if you want to enable urg bit and ack bit, you should set value 48{2^(5-1) + 2^(6-1)}.

swCpuAclIpProtoIDOption.name: swCpuAclIpProtoIDOption
swCpuAclIpProtoIDOption.description: Specifies if the switch will examine each frame's Protocol ID field or not.

swCpuAclIpProtoIDMask.name: swCpuAclIpProtoIDMask
swCpuAclIpProtoIDMask.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the IP protocol ID and the mask options behind the IP header.

swCpuAclIpRowStatus.name: swCpuAclIpRowStatus
swCpuAclIpRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swCpuAclPktContMaskTable.name: swCpuAclPktContMaskTable
swCpuAclPktContMaskTable.description: This table contains user-defined software ACL information. Access profiles will be created on the switch to define which part of each incoming frame's user-defined part of the packet header will be examined by the switch. Masks entered will be combined with the values the switch finds in the specified frame header fields.

swCpuAclPktContMaskOffset0to15.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the packet content (Offset0to15) and the mask options.

swCpuAclPktContMaskOffset16to31.name: swCpuAclPktContMaskOffset16to31
swCpuAclPktContMaskOffset16to31.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the packet content (Offset16to31) and the mask options.

swCpuAclPktContMaskOffset32to47.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the packet content (Offset32to47) and the mask options.

swCpuAclPktContMaskOffset48to63.name: swCpuAclPktContMaskOffset48to63
swCpuAclPktContMaskOffset48to63.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the packet content (Offset48to63) and the mask options.

swCpuAclPktContMaskOffset64to79.name: swCpuAclPktContMaskOffset64to79
swCpuAclPktContMaskOffset64to79.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the packet content (Offset64to79) and the mask options.

swCpuAclPktContMaskRowStatus.name: swCpuAclPktContMaskRowStatus
swCpuAclPktContMaskRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swCpuAclIpv6MaskTable.name: swCpuAclIpv6MaskTable
swCpuAclIpv6MaskTable.description: This table contains IPv6 software ACL mask information. An access profile will be created on the switch to define which part of each incoming frame's IPv6 part of the packet header will be examined by switch. Masks entered will be combined with the values the switch finds in the specified frame header fields.

swCpuAclIpv6MaskEntry.name: swCpuAclIpv6MaskEntry
swCpuAclIpv6MaskEntry.description: A list of information about user-defined software ACLs.

swCpuAclIpv6MaskProfileID.name: swCpuAclIpv6MaskProfileID
swCpuAclIpv6MaskProfileID.description: The ID of the software ACL mask entry, which is unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swCpuAclIpv6MaskClass.name: swCpuAclIpv6MaskClass
swCpuAclIpv6MaskClass.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the IPv6 class field and the mask options.

swCpuAclIpv6MaskFlowlabel.name: swCpuAclIpv6MaskFlowlabel
swCpuAclIpv6MaskFlowlabel.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the IPv6 flowlabel field and the mask options.

swCpuAclIpv6IpAddrMaskState.name: swCpuAclIpv6IpAddrMaskState
swCpuAclIpv6IpAddrMaskState.description: This object indicates the status of IPv6 address mask. other (1) - Neither source IPv6 address nor destination IPv6 address are masked. dst-ipv6-addr (2) - Packets will be filtered if this destination IPv6 address is identified as a match in received frames. src-ipv6-addr (3) - Packets will be filtered if this source IPv6 address is identified as a match in received frames. dst-src-ipv6-addr (4) - Packets will be filtered if this destination or source IPv6 address is identified as a match in received frames.

swCpuAclIpv6MaskSrcIpv6Mask.name: swCpuAclIpv6MaskSrcIpv6Mask
swCpuAclIpv6MaskSrcIpv6Mask.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the source IPv6 address and the mask options. This should be a 16 byte octet string.

swCpuAclIpv6MaskDstIpv6Mask.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the destination IPv6 address and the mask options. This should be a 16 byte octet string.

swCpuAclEtherRuleAccessID.name: swCpuAclEtherRuleAccessID

swCpuAclEtherRuleVlan.name: swCpuAclEtherRuleVlan

swCpuAclEtherRuleSrcMacAddress.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to the packets with this source MAC address.

swCpuAclEtherRuleDstMacAddress.name: swCpuAclEtherRuleDstMacAddress
swCpuAclEtherRuleDstMacAddress.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to the packets with this destination MAC address.

swCpuAclEtherRule8021P.name: swCpuAclEtherRule8021P
swCpuAclEtherRule8021P.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to packets with this 802.1p priority value. A value of -1 indicates that this node is not actively used.

swCpuAclEtherRuleEtherType.name: swCpuAclEtherRuleEtherType
swCpuAclEtherRuleEtherType.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to packets with this 802.1Q Ethernet type value in the packet header.

swCpuAclEtherRulePermit.description: This object indicates if the result of the packet examination is to 'permit' or 'deny'. swCpuAclIpRuleProtocol.name: swCpuAclIpRuleProtocol
swCpuAclIpRuleProtocol.description: Specifies the IP protocol which has been configured in swCpuAclIpEntry.

swCpuAclIpRuleType.name: swCpuAclIpRuleType
swCpuAclIpRuleType.description: Specifies the rule applies to the value of ICMP type traffic. A value of -1 indicates that this node is not actively used.

swCpuAclIpRuleCode.name: swCpuAclIpRuleCode
swCpuAclIpRuleCode.description: Specifies the rule applies to the value of ICMP code traffic. A value of -1 indicates that this node is not actively used.

swCpuAclIpRuleSrcPort.name: swCpuAclIpRuleSrcPort
swCpuAclIpRuleSrcPort.description: Specifies the rule applies to the range of TCP/UDP source ports. A value of -1 indicates that this node is not actively used.

swCpuAclIpRuleDstPort.name: swCpuAclIpRuleDstPort
swCpuAclIpRuleDstPort.description: Specifies the range of TCP/UDP destination ports. A value of -1 indicates that this node is not actively used.

swCpuAclIpRuleFlagBits.description: A value which indicates the set of TCP flags that this entity may potentially offer. The value is a sum of flag bits. This sum initially takes the value zero. swCpuAclIpRuleUserMask.name: swCpuAclIpRuleUserMask
swCpuAclIpRuleUserMask.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the IP protocol ID and the range of options behind the IP header.

swCpuAclIpRuleRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swCpuAclIpRulePort.name: swCpuAclIpRulePort
swCpuAclIpRulePort.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to port(s).

swCpuAclPktContRuleTable.description: This table contains user-defined software ACL rule information.

swCpuAclPktContRuleOffset0to15.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the user-defined packet.

swCpuAclPktContRuleOffset48to63.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the user-defined packet.

swCpuAclPktContRuleOffset64to79.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the user-defined packet.

swCpuAclIpv6RuleEntry.description: A list of information about the ACL rule of the user-defined part of each packet.

swAclMeterTable.name: swAclMeterTable
swAclMeterTable.description: This table is used to configure the flow-based metering function. The access rule must first be created before the parameters of this function can be applied. Users may set the preferred bandwidth for this rule, in Kbps; once the bandwidth has been exceeded, overflow packets will be either dropped or set for a drop precedence, depending on user configuration.

swAclMeterEntry.name: swAclMeterEntry
swAclMeterEntry.description: This entry displays parameters and configurations set for the flow metering function.

swAclMeterProfileID.name: swAclMeterProfileID
swAclMeterProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL mask entry is unique in the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swAclMeterAccessID.name: swAclMeterAccessID
swAclMeterAccessID.description: The ID of the ACL rule entry as related to the swAclMeterProfileID.

swAclMeterRate.name: swAclMeterRate
swAclMeterRate.description: Specifies the committed bandwidth in Kbps for the flow. NOTE: 1. Specifying 0 will disable this flow meter setting. 2. Users must set the swAclMeterActionForRateExceed object to activate this entry.

swAclMeterActionForRateExceed.name: swAclMeterActionForRateExceed
swAclMeterActionForRateExceed.description: Specifies the action to take for those packets exceeding the committed rate. NOTE: Users must also set the swAclMeterRate to activate this entry.

swAclMeterRemarkDscp.name: swAclMeterRemarkDscp
swAclMeterRemarkDscp.description: Mark the packet with a specified DSCP. It can be set when swAclMeterActionForRateExceed sets remark-dscp (3).

swAclMeterBurstSize.name: swAclMeterBurstSize
swAclMeterBurstSize.description: This specifies the burst size for the single rate two color mode. The unit is Kbytes. That is to say, 1 means 1kbytes. The set value range is 0..n, the value n is determined by project, the value of 0 means to delete this flow_meter setting.

swAclMeterMode.name: swAclMeterMode
swAclMeterMode.description: tr-tcm: two rate three color mode; sr-tcm: single rate three color mode.

swAclMeterTrtcmCir.name: swAclMeterTrtcmCir
swAclMeterTrtcmCir.description: Specifies the 'committed information rate' of 'two rate three color mode'. The unit is Kbps.

swAclMeterTrtcmCbs.name: swAclMeterTrtcmCbs
swAclMeterTrtcmCbs.description: Specifies the 'committed burst size' of 'two rate three color mode'. 1. The unit is Kbytes. That is to say, 1 means 1Kbytes. 2. This parameter is an optional parameter. The default value is 4*1024. 3. The max set value is 16*1024.

swAclMeterTrtcmPir.name: swAclMeterTrtcmPir
swAclMeterTrtcmPir.description: Specifies the 'Peak Information Rate' of 'two rate three color mode'. The unit is Kbps.

swAclMeterTrtcmPbs.name: swAclMeterTrtcmPbs
swAclMeterTrtcmPbs.description: Specifies the 'peak burst size' of 'two rate three color mode'. 1. The unit is Kbytes. That is to say, 1 means 1kbytes. 2. This parameter is an optional parameter. The default value is 4*1024. 3. The max set value is 16*1024.

swAclMeterTrtcmColorMode.name: swAclMeterTrtcmColorMode
swAclMeterTrtcmColorMode.description: Specifies the meter mode. The default is color-blind mode. The final color of the packet is determined by the initial color of the packet and the metering result.

swAclMeterTrtcmConformState.name: swAclMeterTrtcmConformState
swAclMeterTrtcmConformState.description: Specifies the action state when packet is in 'green color'. permit: permit the packet. replace-dscp: change the DSCP value of packet.

swAclMeterTrtcmConformReplaceDscp.name: swAclMeterTrtcmConformReplaceDscp
swAclMeterTrtcmConformReplaceDscp.description: Specifies the DSCP value of the packet when the packet is in 'green color'.

swAclMeterTrtcmConformCounterState.name: swAclMeterTrtcmConformCounterState
swAclMeterTrtcmConformCounterState.description: Specifies the counter state when the packet is in 'green color'. 1. This is optional. The default is 'disable'. 2. The resource may be limited so that the counter can not be turned on. The limitation is project dependent. 3. counter will be cleared when the function is disabled.

swAclMeterTrtcmExceedState.name: swAclMeterTrtcmExceedState
swAclMeterTrtcmExceedState.description: Specifies the action state when packet is in 'yellow color'. permit: permit the packet. replace-dscp: change the DSCP value of the packet. drop: drop the packet.

swAclMeterTrtcmExceedReplaceDscp.name: swAclMeterTrtcmExceedReplaceDscp
swAclMeterTrtcmExceedReplaceDscp.description: Specifies the DSCP value of packet when packet is in 'yellow color'.

swAclMeterTrtcmExceedCounterState.name: swAclMeterTrtcmExceedCounterState
swAclMeterTrtcmExceedCounterState.description: Specifies the counter state when packet is in 'yellow color'. 1. This is optional. The default is 'disable'. 2. swAclMeterSrtcmCir.name: swAclMeterSrtcmCir

swAclMeterSrtcmCbs.name: swAclMeterSrtcmCbs

swAclMeterSrtcmEbs.name: swAclMeterSrtcmEbs
swAclMeterSrtcmEbs.description: Specifies the 'Excess burst size' of 'single rate three color mode'. 1. The unit is Kbytes. That is to say, 1 means 1kbytes. 2. The max set value is 16*1024.

swAclMeterSrtcmColorMode.name: swAclMeterSrtcmColorMode
swAclMeterSrtcmColorMode.description: Specifies the meter mode. The default is color-blind mode. The final color of packet is determined by the initial color of the packet and the metering result.
